<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF8"?>
<xsl:stylesheet version="1.0" xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform">

  <xsl:template match="surveyGDB">
    <html class="no-js" lang="en">
      <head> 
        <meta charset="utf-8" />
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
        <title>Survey Editing Report</title>
        <xsl:call-template name="stylesheet" /> 
      </head>
      <body>
        <div class="container">
          <xsl:call-template name="header" /><!-- jumbotron -->

          <!--  Background --> 
          <h2>Background</h2>
          <p>Once a survey has been completed and imported from the instrument file into GIS, there are several critical steps in post-processing a survey that involve manual editing.  This report provides descriptive information of the changes to the point cloud from which a surface was generated, the lines present in the survey, and changes to the TIN surface.</p> 

          <p>Since editing can be performed at different times during the point collection and post-processing workflow these summaries are not an indicator of survey quality.</p>

          <!-- Point and Line Editing -->   
          <div class="panel panel-default"> 
            <div class="panel-heading"><div class="panel-title"><h2>Point and line editing</h2></div></div>
            <div class="panel-body">
              <p>Crews have the opportunity to adjust point descriptions and generate lines during post processing.</p>
              <h3>Total Points: <xsl:value-of select="sum(/surveyGDB/tables/table[name='QaQcPoints']/records/record/Count)"/></h3>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Point Editing Table -->
          <div class="metric">
            <h3>Point Editing Summary</h3>
            <table id="point-editing-summary" class="table">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Code</th>
                  <th>Count, First</th>
                  <th>Count, Last</th>
                  <th>% Added</th>
                  <th>% Deleted</th>
                  <th>Edited</th>
                  <th>Points Collected</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>                
              <tbody>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <!-- Line Editing Table -->
          <div class="metric">
            <h3>Line Editing Summary</h3>
            <table id="line-editing-summary" class="table">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Code</th>
                  <th>Total Length, First</th>
                  <th>Total Length, Last</th>
                  <th>% Added</th>
                  <th>% Deleted</th>
                  <th>Edited</th>
                  <th>Lines Collected</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>    


          <!-- TIN editing -->
          <div class="panel panel-default"> 
            <div class="panel-heading"><div class="panel-title"><h2>Tin Editing</h2></div></div>
            <div class="panel-body">
              <!-- variables derived from TIN summary table, using JS? -->    
              <p>'<xsl:value-of select="/surveyGDB/tables/table/records/record/FinalTIN" />' is the final TIN and it was last processed on <span id="tin-last-timestamp">[LAST TIMESTAMP]</span> in <span id="tin-minutes">[FIRST - LAST TIMESTAMP]</span>.</p>
              <p>TINs are made of triangular facets that have nodes where the facet endpoints meet. These nodes can be generated from points collected by crews or artificial nodes that were generated by GIS during the TIN generation.</p>
              <p>In this survey, edits included the addition of <span id="nodes-added">[0]</span> nodes and deletion of <span id="nodes-deleted">[0]</span> nodes for a net change of <span id="nodes-delta">[0]</span>.  <span id="nodes-topo">[0]</span> of the nodes originate from Topo Points.  There are <span id="nodes-not-topo">[0]</span> topo points that are not nodes in the TIN. [0] node was changed in a breakline.  A dam <span id="dams-remove"></span> removed during TIN editing and a facet <span id="facets-remove"></span> removed. TIN editing changed the minimum node elevation by <span id="nodes-Zmax">[0]</span> and the maximum node elevation by <span id="nodes-Zmin">[0]</span>.</p>
              <p>There are <span id="BL-length">[0]</span> of breaklines that were used in the TIN generation and <span id="BL-cross">[0]</span> were crossed at the time of final TIN validation.</p>    
            </div>
            
            <!-- TIN node Editing summary table -->
            <div class="metric"> 
              <h3>Node Editing Summary</h3>    
              <table id="node-editing-summary" class="table">
                <thead>
                  <tr>
                    <th>Code</th>
                    <th>First TIN</th>
                    <th>Last TIN</th>
                    <th>% Addition</th>
                    <th>% Deletion</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>

            <!-- Image Snapshots -->
            <div class="panel panel-default"> 
              <h2>Review Images</h2>
              <xsl:for-each select="/surveyGDB/tables/table[name='MapImages']/records/record">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <img src="{FilePath}" />
                    <p><xsl:value-of select="Title" /></p>
                </div>
              </xsl:for-each>
            </div>
              
            </div>
          </div>
          <xsl:call-template name="javascript" />
          <xsl:call-template name="JSON" />
        </body>
      </html>
    </xsl:template>

    <xsl:template name="header">
      <div class="jumbotron">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-12">
            <h1>Survey Editing Report</h1>
            <h3>Created on: <xsl:value-of select="/surveyGDB/xmlcreated" /></h3>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-md-12">
                <h2><xsl:value-of select="/surveyGDB/tables/table/records/record/Watershed" /></h2>    
                <ul class="list-unstyled">
                  <li>Visit ID: <xsl:value-of select="/surveyGDB/tables/table/records/record/VisitID" /></li>
                  <li>Site Name: <xsl:value-of select="/surveyGDB/tables/table/records/record/SiteID" /></li>
                  <li>Sampled: <xsl:value-of select="/surveyGDB/tables/table/records/record/SurveyDate" /></li>
                  <li>Survey GDB Name: <xsl:value-of select="/surveyGDB/filename" /></li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6"><img class="img"></img></div> <!-- site map? -->
      </div> 
    </xsl:template>

    <xsl:template name="JSON">
     <script id="ReportJSONData" type="application/json"><xsl:value-of select="/surveyGDB/JSON"/></script>
   </xsl:template>

   <xsl:template name="javascript">
    <script src="tmp/editing_report.js?__inline=true"></script>
  </xsl:template>

  <xsl:template name="stylesheet">
    <link href="tmp/editing_report.css?__inline=true" rel="stylesheet" />
  </xsl:template>
</xsl:stylesheet>